# Olivetti M20 FUZIX Port — TODO

## Done
  - Kernel boots, mounts root filesystem, starts /init
  - exec binary loading (syscall_exec32.c + coff2aout + plt_relocate)
  - crt0, FUZIX libc, syscall wrappers for Z8001
  - /init with fork/exec/waitpid loop
  - V7 shell (/bin/sh) boots with prompt, builtins, external commands
  - dofork, switchin/switchout, signal delivery (VDSO unwind)
  - HD driver (BIOS disk_io)
  - coff2aout: R_IMM32 + R_IMM32_NORELAX relocations with addends
  - CRT video console via BIOS PROM put_char (0x84000080)
  - Keyboard driver: i8251A at 0xA1, polled from timer, CP/M-8000 scan code table
  - 30 userland utilities built and working (ls, echo, cat, grep, etc.)
  - PATH search works (shell finds commands in /bin without full path)
  - Reboot via BIOS cold_boot entry (0x8400008C)
  - Full init with login/getty — boots to login prompt, /etc/rc runs at boot
  - 100+ userland utilities via build-filesystem-ng (basefs, util, V7 cmd)
  - /etc configs (passwd, group, inittab, termcap, rc scripts, mtab, fstab)
  - Read-write filesystem (CMDLINE "hda rw")
  - Boot messages on CRT (kprintf writes to both serial and CRT)
  - Standard device numbering (major 0=hd, major 1=fd, matching basefs.pkg)

## Bugs fixed this session

### coff2aout: .eh_frame mistaken for .data (Standalone/coff2aout.c)
  GCC generates .eh_frame sections with the STYP_DATA flag. coff2aout matched
  sections by flags, so .eh_frame (last section with DATA flag) overwrote the
  real .data section info. All initialized pointers in .data were zero at runtime.
  Fix: match sections by name (".text", ".data", ".bss") instead of flags.

### Syscall generator: missing sign extension for pid_t (Library/tools/syscall_z8000.c)
  waitpid(pid, ...) and kill(pid, ...) pass pid_t as 16-bit signed.  The generator
  zero-extended all 16-bit args (`clr r2; ld r3, val`), so pid=-1 became 0x0000FFFF
  (65535) instead of 0xFFFFFFFF (-1).  waitpid(-1,...) never matched any child;
  the shell hung after every external command.
  Fix: added 's' arg type that generates sign extension via `sra r2, #15`.
  Applied to waitpid (syscall 55) and kill (syscall 39).

### Syscall generator: memalloc return truncated (Library/tools/syscall_z8000.c)
  memalloc (syscall 64) returns a 32-bit pointer, but the generator emitted
  `ld r2, r3` which truncates to 16 bits (loses the segment).  Pointers from
  calloc/malloc pointed to segment 0 (kernel memory), causing EFAULT on any
  I/O to the allocated buffer (e.g. readdir's read() in ls).
  Fix: added memalloc to `returns_ptr` list (skips `ld r2, r3`).

### Syscall generator: memfree takes pointer, not word (Library/tools/syscall_z8000.c)
  memfree (syscall 65) takes a pointer argument but was typed as 'w' (16-bit).
  Fix: changed to 'l' (32-bit pointer).

### Library: USE_SYSMALLOC incompatible with segmented Z8001 (Library/libs/Makefile.z8000)
  USE_SYSMALLOC makes malloc call the memalloc syscall, which uses kmalloc to
  allocate from the kernel heap (segment 0x82).  On Z8001, user processes run in
  different segments (e.g. 0x8D).  The kernel's valaddr rejects kernel-segment
  pointers passed by user code, causing EFAULT.
  Fix: removed -DUSE_SYSMALLOC.  malloc now uses sbrk to grow the user's own
  data segment, which is always in the correct segment.

### Syscall wrappers: errno symbol mismatch (Library/tools/syscall_z8000.c)
  All syscall wrappers wrote error codes to `errno` (assembly symbol) but C code
  read from `_errno` (C symbol with underscore prefix). These resolved to different
  addresses. errno was NEVER set from C's perspective — every perror() said "Success",
  every `if (errno == ENOEXEC)` check failed, init couldn't fall back to /bin/sh
  for shell scripts.
  Fix: generator now emits `ld _errno, r1` instead of `ld errno, r1`.

### crt0: environ loaded as value instead of address (Library/libs/crt0_z8000.S)
  `ldl rr2, rr14(#8)` loaded the VALUE at ISP+8 (= envp[0], first env string pointer).
  But `_environ` must be the ADDRESS of the envp array (ISP+8 itself).  With no
  environment (stub init), envp[0]=NULL so _environ=NULL — worked by accident.
  With real environment from full init, _environ pointed to a string like
  "PATH=/bin:/usr/bin" instead of the pointer array — shell crashed in sh_getenv.
  Fix: `ldl rr2, rr14; addl rr2, #8` computes address instead of loading value.
  Same fix applied to crt0nostdio_z8000.S.

### Device numbering: swapped major numbers (devices.c, config.h)
  Original M20 had major 0=fd, major 1=hd (BOOTDEVICE=0x0100).  Standard FUZIX
  (basefs.pkg) uses major 0=hd, major 1=fd.  prtroot showed /dev/fd0 as root.
  Fix: swapped device table entries, BOOTDEVICE=0x0000, BOOTDEVICENAMES="hd#,fd#".
  Root mounts ro by default; /etc/rc does fsck then remount rw.

